task.action:
In `src/components/tables/expenses/ExpenseTable.tsx`:

1. Import `Badge` from `@/components/ui/badge` and `TagInput` from `@/components/shared/TagInput`.

2. Create a `TagsCell` component (above or near `CellContent`) that handles both read and edit modes:
   ```tsx
   const TagsCell = ({ getValue, row, table }: any) => {
     const tags = getValue() as { id: string; name: string; color: string }[] | undefined;
     const tableMeta = table.options.meta;
     const isEditing = tableMeta?.editedRows[row.id];

     if (isEditing) {
       return (
         <div className="min-w-[180px]">
           <TagInput
             selectedTagIds={tags?.map(t => t.id) || []}
             onChange={(tagIds) => {
               // We need to update with full tag objects for display
               // TagInput uses useTagsQuery internally, so we can reconstruct
               tableMeta?.updateData(row.index, "tags", tagIds);
             }}
           />
         </div>
       );
     }

     if (!tags || tags.length === 0) return <span className="text-muted-foreground">-</span>;

     return (
       <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-1 max-w-[150px]">
         {tags.slice(0, 2).map(tag => (
           <Badge key={tag.id} variant="outline" className="text-[10px] px-1.5 py-0 h-4 gap-1">
             <span className="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0" style={{ backgroundColor: tag.color }} />
             {tag.name}
           </Badge>
         ))}
         {tags.length > 2 && (
           <span className="text-[10px] text-muted-foreground">+{tags.length - 2}</span>
         )}
       </div>
     );
   };
   ```

   **Important note on the `onChange` handler**: The `TagInput` component calls `onChange(tagIds: string[])` with just IDs. But for `saveRow` we need the IDs. So when `TagsCell` receives the new tagIds from TagInput, it should store just the tagIds array via `updateData`, and `saveRow` should read this properly.

   The simplest approach: store the tagIds as an array directly via `updateData(row.index, "tags", tagIds)`. Then in `saveRow`, check if `updatedRow.tags` is an array of strings (tagIds) or array of objects, and handle accordingly:
   ```tsx
   tagIds: Array.isArray(updatedRow.tags)
     ? typeof updatedRow.tags[0] === 'string'
       ? updatedRow.tags  // already tagIds from edit
       : updatedRow.tags.map((t: any) => t.id)  // original objects
     : [],
   ```

3. Add the tags column to the `columns` array, after the `description` column and before the `edit` column:
   ```tsx
   columnHelper.accessor("tags", {
     header: "Tags",
     cell: TagsCell,
   }),
   ```

4. Widen the `updateData` callback's `value` parameter type from `string` to `any`:
   ```tsx
   const updateData = useCallback((rowIndex: number, columnId: string, value: any) => {
   ```

5. Update `saveRow` to include `tagIds` in the update payload:
   ```tsx
   tagIds: Array.isArray(updatedRow.tags)
     ? typeof updatedRow.tags[0] === 'string'
       ? updatedRow.tags
       : updatedRow.tags.map((t: any) => t.id)
     : [],
   ```
